Object.Name: NC-Zykluszeit (TNcyc)
Control unit cycle time (TNcyc)
Object.Comment: Die NC-Zykluszeit definiert die zyklischen Intervalle whrend der die NC neue Sollwerte zur Verfgung stellt. Die NC-Zykluszeit soll whrend der CP2 vom Master zum Slave bertragen werden und wird whrend CP3 aktiv. Die NC-Zykluszeit soll ein ganzzahliges Vielfaches der der Kommunikations-Zykluszeit sein. tNcyc = tScyc * n [n =1,2,3,4...]

The control unit cycle time defines the cyclic intervals during which the control unit makes new command values available. The control unit cycle time shall be transferred from the master to the slave during CP2 and becomes active in the slave during CP3. The control unit cycle time should be an integer multiple of the communication cycle time. tNcyc = tScyc * n [n =1,2,3,4...]

Object.Name: Kommunikations-Zykluszeit (tSync)
Communication cycle time (tSync)
Object.Comment: Die Kommunikations-Zykluszeit der Schnittstelle beschreibt die Intevalle wrend deren die zyklischen Daten bertragen werden. Sie ist als 62 us, 125 us, 250 us und bis zu 65000 s in Schritten von 250 s definiert. Die Kommunikations-Zykluszeit wird whrend CP2 vom Master zum Slave bertragen und wird in beiden whrend CP3 aktiv.

The communication cycle time of the interface defines the intervals during which the cyclic data are transferred. It is defined as 62 us, 125 us, 250 us, ..., up to 65000 s in steps of 250 s. The communication cycle time shall be transferred from the master to the slave during CP2 and becomes active in both during CP3.

Object.Name: Klasse 1 Diagnose (C1D)
Class 1 diagnostic (C1D)
Object.Comment:
Drive Abschalt-Fehler

Eine Fehlersituation der Klasse C1D fhrt zu folgendem:

  • Eine bestmgliche Verzgerung gefolgt von einem Drehmomentabbau bei nmin.
  • Das Bit Drive Shut-down Error fr C1D (Bit 13) des DriveStatus wird auf '1' gesetzt. Das Fehler-Bit wird erst vom Drive auf '0' zurckgesetzt wenn keine Fehler der Klasse C1D mehr existieren und das Kommando 'reset class 1 diagnostic' (IDN 00099) vom Drive ber den Service-Kanal empfangen wurde.

Drive shut-down error

A drive error situation of class C1D leads to the following:

  • A best case deceleration followed by torque release at nmin.
  • The drive shut-down error bit for C1D is set to '1' in the drive status (bit 13). The error bit is reset to '0' by the drive only when no errors of C1D exists and after the command 'reset class 1 diagnostic' (IDN 00099) has been received by the drive via the service channel.

Object.Name: Klasse 1 Diagnose (C2D)
Class 2 diagnostic (C2D)
Object.Comment: Abschaltwarnung (Warnung) Wenn in C2D eine Warnung aktiviert oder zurckgenommen wird, setzt dies das Wechsel-Bit fr C2D (Bit 12) im Status-Wort auf eien binre 1 Wenn der C2D ber den Service-kanal gelesen wird, wird das C2D-Wechsel-Bit zurckgenommen und auf 0 zurckgesetzt. Die mit C2D verknpfte Maske kann die Auswirkungen des Wechselbits im DriveStatus maskieren wenn sich eine Warnbedingung ndert (siehe IDN 00097). (Durch C2D definierte Bits C2D sind auch durch IDNs definiert.)

Shut-down warning (warning) When a warning is activated or canceled in the C2D, this sets the change bit for C2D in the drive status (bit 12) to a binary 1. When the C2D is read via the service channel, the C2D change bit is canceled and reset to 0. The mask associated with C2D can mask the effects on the change bit of the drive status when a warning condition changes (see IDN 00097). (Bits defined by C2D are also defined by IDNs.)

Object.Name: Telegram type
Telegram type
Object.Comment: Der Telegramm-Typ erlaubt die Auswahl zwischen Standard- und Applikations-Telegrammen.
The telegram type allows selection between standard telegrams and application telegrams.

Object.Name: Konfigurationsliste der AT
Configuration list of AT
Object.Comment: Die IDN-Liste beinhaltet die IDNs deren Operationsdaten im AT im Applicationstelegramm zyklisch bertragen werden. Der Drive muss diese Liste nur untersttzen, wenn er das Anwendungstelegramm in seinem Parameter Tegramm-Typ erlaubt (siehe IDN 00015). Nur Operationsdaten die in der IDN-Liste der Konfigurationsdaten im AT (IDN 00187) vorhanden sind, sind als zyklische Daten zugelassen.

This IDN list contains the IDNs whose operation data will be transmitted cyclically in the AT in an application telegram. The drive needs to support this list only if it allows the application telegram in its telegram type parameter (see IDN 00015). Only operation data which are present in the "IDN list of configurable data in the AT" (IDN 00187) are allowed as cyclic data.

Object.Name: IDN-List aller Operation-Daten
IDN-list of all operation data
Object.Comment: Alle IDNs aller Operationsdaten, Prozedur-Kommandos, Parameter usw. eines gegebenen Drives sind in dieser IDN-Liste gespeichert.
All IDNs of all operation data, procedure commands, parameters etc. of a given drive are stored in this IDN-list.

Object.Name: IDN-List der Operations-Daten fr CP2
IDN-list of operation data for CP2
Object.Comment: IDNs aller Operationsdaten die fr CP2 bentigt werden sind wrend CP2 in dieser Liste gespeichert Die Verarbeitung dieser List ist vor dem Umschalten zu CP3 erforderlich.
IDNs of all operation data needed for CP2 are stored in this IDN-list and must be transferred during CP2. Processing this list is required before switching to CP3.

Object.Name: IDN-List der Operations-Daten fr CP3
IDN-list of operation data for CP3
Object.Comment: IDNs aller Operationsdaten die fr CP3 bentigt werden sind wrend CP3 in dieser Liste gespeichert. Die Verarbeitung dieser List ist vor dem Umschalten zu CP4 erforderlich.
IDNs of all operation data needed for CP3 are stored in this IDN-list and must be transferred during CP3. Processing this list is required before switching to CP4.

Object.Name: IDN-List der Operation-Daten fr CP4
IDN-list of operation data for CP4
Object.Comment: IDNs aller Operationsdaten die fr CP3 bentigt werden sind wrend CP3 in dieser Liste gespeichert.
IDNs of all operational data which can be changed during CP4 are stored in this IDN-list.

Object.Name: IDN-Liste der ungltigen Operations-Daten fr CP2
IDN-list of invalid operation data for CP2
Object.Comment: IDNs die in der "IDN-Liste der Operation-Daten fr CP2" (IDN 00018) enthalten und die vom Drive vor dem Umschalten von CP2 (SafeOp) zu CP3 (PreOp) als ungltig betrachtet werden sind in dieser IDN-Liste gespeichert (siehe IDN 00127).

IDNs which are in the list "IDN-list of operation data for CP2" (IDN 00018) and which are considered invalid by the drive prior to switchover from CP2 (SafeOp) to CP3 (PreOp) are stored in this IDN-list (see IDN 00127).

Object.Name: IDN-Liste der ungltigen Operations-Daten fr CP3
IDN-list of invalid operation data for CP3
Object.Comment: IDNs die in der "IDN-Liste der Operation-Daten fr CP3" (IDN 00019) enthalten und die vom Drive vor dem Umschalten von CP3 (PreOp) zu CP4 (Op) als ungltig betrachtet werden sind in dieser IDN-Liste gespeichert (siehe IDN ?????).

IDNs which are in the list "IDN-list of operation data for CP3" (IDN 00019) and which are considered invalid by the drive prior to switchover from CP3 (PreOp) to CP4 (Op) are stored in this IDN-list (see IDN ?????).

Object.Name: Konfigurations-Liste der MDT
Configuration list of MDT
Object.Comment: Diese IDN-Liste enthlt die IDNs deren Daten in den MDT zyklisch in einem Applikations-Telegramm bertragen werden. Der Drive muss diese Liste nur untersttzen, wenn er das Applikations-Telegramm in seinen Telegrammtyp-Parametern erlaubt siehe IDN 00015). Nur Operationsdaten die in der "IDN-Liste der konfigurierbaren Daten der MDT" (IDN 00188) enthalten sind, sind als zyklische Daten zugelassen.

This IDN list contains the IDNs whose operation data will be transmitted cyclically in the MDT in an application telegram. The drive needs to support this list only when it allows the application telegram in its telegram type parameter (see IDN 00015). Only operation data which are present in the "IDN-list of configurable data in the MDT" (IDN 00188) are allowed as cyclic data.

Object.Name: IDN-Liste aller Prozedur-Kommandos
IDN-list of all procedure commands
Object.Comment: Alle IDNs aller Drive-Prozedur-Kommandos sind in dieser Liste gespeichert.
All IDNs of all drive procedure commands are stored in this IDN-list.

Object.Name: MDT-Fehlerzhler
MDT error counter
Object.Comment: Der MDT-Fehlerzhler zhlt alle ungltigen MDTs (Master-Data-Telegramme) in der Kommunikations-Phase 4 (siehe auch Fehlerbehandlung in Kapitel 09). Falls mehr als zwei aufeinanderfolgende MDTs ungltig sind, werden nicht mehr als zwei ungltige MDTs gezhlt. Der MDT-Fehlerzhler zhlt bis zu einem Maximum con 216 - . Die bedeutet, dass wenn ein Wert von 65535 in den Zhler gesetzt wird, eine verrauschte bertragung ber einen langen Zeitraum stattgefunden hat.

The MDT error counter counts all invalid MDTs (Master Data Telegramms) in communication phase 4 (Refer also to error handling in clause 09). In cases where more than two consecutive MDTs are invalid, the invalid MDTs over two are not counted. The MDT error counter counts to a maximum of 216 - 1. This means that if a value of 65 535 is set in the counter, there may have been a noisy transmission over a long period of time.

Object.Name: Hersteller-Version
Manufacturer Version
Object.Comment: Die Operations-Daten des Herstellers-Version beinhalten die the aktuelle Firmware-Version und weitere Informationen ber das Gert. Die Struktur der Hersteller-version ist nicht festgelegt.
The operation data of the manufacturer version contains the actual firmware version and additional information of the device. The structure of the manufacturer version is not specified.

Object.Name: Hardware-Version
Hardware version
Object.Comment: The Operations-Daten der Hardware-Version beinhalten die aktuelle Hardware-Version und weitere Informationen ber das Gert.
The operation data of the hardware version contains the actual hardware version and additional information of the device.

Object.Name: Hauptbetriebsart
Primary operation mode
Object.Comment: Die Betriebsart (Hauptbetriebsart oder Nebenbetriebsart 1 bis 3) wird ber Bit 9 und 8 des DriveControlWords der MDT ausgewhlt. Die aktivierte Betriebsart wird von Bit 9 ud 8 des DriveStatusWord der AT angezeigt.

The Operation Mode (Primary Operation Mode or Secondarey Operatin Mode 1 to 3) is selected via bits 9 and 8 in the DriveControlWord word of the MDT. The activated operation mode is indicated by bits 9 and 8 of the DriveStatusWord in the AT.

Object.Name: Nebenbetriebsart 1
Secondary operation mode 1
Object.Comment: Die Betriebsart (Hauptbetriebsart oder Nebenbetriebsart 1 bis 3) wird ber Bit 9 und 8 des DriveControlWords der MDT ausgewhlt. Die aktivierte Betriebsart wird von Bit 9 ud 8 des DriveStatusWord der AT angezeigt.

The Operation Mode (Primary Operation Mode or Secondarey Operatin Mode 1 to 3) is selected via bits 9 and 8 in the DriveControlWord word of the MDT. The activated operation mode is indicated by bits 9 and 8 of the DriveStatusWord in the AT.

Object.Name: Nebenbetriebsart 2
Secondary operation mode 2
Object.Comment: Die Betriebsart (Hauptbetriebsart oder Nebenbetriebsart 1 bis 3) wird ber Bit 9 und 8 des DriveControlWords der MDT ausgewhlt. Die aktivierte Betriebsart wird von Bit 9 ud 8 des DriveStatusWord der AT angezeigt.

The Operation Mode (Primary Operation Mode or Secondarey Operatin Mode 1 to 3) is selected via bits 9 and 8 in the DriveControlWord word of the MDT. The activated operation mode is indicated by bits 9 and 8 of the DriveStatusWord in the AT.

Object.Name: Nebenbetriebsart 3
Secondary operation mode 3
Object.Comment: Die Betriebsart (Hauptbetriebsart oder Nebenbetriebsart 1 bis 3) wird ber Bit 9 und 8 des DriveControlWords der MDT ausgewhlt. Die aktivierte Betriebsart wird von Bit 9 ud 8 des DriveStatusWord der AT angezeigt.

The Operation Mode (Primary Operation Mode or Secondarey Operatin Mode 1 to 3) is selected via bits 9 and 8 in the DriveControlWord word of the MDT. The activated operation mode is indicated by bits 9 and 8 of the DriveStatusWord in the AT.

Object.Name: Geschwindigkeits-Sollwert
Velocity command value
Object.Comment: In der Betriebsart Geschwindigkeitskontrolle, transferriert die NC Geschwindigkeitssollwerte in den Zeitabstnden der NC-Zykluszeit zum Drive.
In the velocity control operating mode in the drive, the control unit transfers the velocity command values to the drive in the time pattern of the control unit cycle time.

Object.Name: Geschwindigkeits-Istwert 1
Velocity feedback value 1
Object.Comment: Der Geschwindigkeits-Istwert 1 wird vom Drive zur NC transferiert um der NC die periodische Anzeige der Geschwindigkeit zu ermglichen. Geschwindigkeits-Istwert bezieht sich auf den Encoder des Motors.

The velocity feedback value 1 is transferred from the drive to the control unit in order to allow the control unit to periodically display the velocity. The velocity feedback value 1 refers to the motor encoder.

Object.Name: Geschwindigkeits-Polaritten
Velocity polarity parameter
Object.Comment: Dieser Parameter wird benutzt um die Polaritten der Geschwindigkeitsdaten fr spezielle Anwendungen umzuschalten. Die Polaritten werden nicht intern aber extern (am Ein- und Ausgang) eines geschlossenen Regelkreises umgeschaltet. Die Motorwelle rotiert im Uhrzeigersinn, wenn ein positive Geschwindigkeitsdifferenzkommando und keine Umkehrung programmiert ist.

This parameter is used to switch polarities of velocity data for specific applications. Polarities are not switched internally but externally (on the input and output) of a closed loop system. The motor shaft turns clockwise when there is a positive velocity command difference and no inversion is programmed.

Object.Name: Skalierungsart fr Geschwindigkeitsdaten
Velocity data scaling type
Object.Comment: Aus einer Auswahl von Skalierungsarten kann mit dem Parameter Skalierungsart eine ausgewhlt werden. Bit 5 ist fr die ausgewhlten Daten auf 'Minute' zu setzen (siehe auch Bild 67).
A variety of scaling methods can be selected by means of the scaling type parameter. Bit 5 is set to 'minute' for preferred data (see also figure 67)

Object.Name: Wichtungsfaktor fr Geschwindigkeitsdaten
Velocity data scaling factor
Object.Comment: Dieser Parameter definiert den Skalierungsfaktor fr alle Geschwindigkeitsdaten des Drives.
This parameter defines the scaling factor for all velocity data in a drive.

Object.Name: Skalierungsexponent der Geschwindigkeitsdaten
Velocity data scaling exponent
Object.Comment: Dieser Parameter definiert den Skalierungsexponent fr alle fr alle Geschwindigkeitsdaten des Drives.
This parameter defines the scaling exponent for all velocity data in a drive.

Object.Name: Lagesollert
Position command value
Object.Comment: Wrend der Betriebsart Positionskontrolle, werden die Positionssollwerte im Zeitabstand der NC-Zykluszeit von der NC zum Drive bertragen according.
During the position control drive operation mode, the position command values are transferred from the control unit to the drive according to the time pattern of the control unit cycle.

Object.Name: Lage-Istwert 1 (Motorgeber)
Position feedback value 1 (motor feedback)
Object.Comment: Der Lage-Istwert 1 vird vom Drive zur NC bertragen so das es der NC mglicht ist wen erforderlich Block-Stepping auszufhren und die Position anzuzeigen.
The position feedback value 1 is transferred from the drive to the control unit so that it is possible for the control unit to perform block stepping and display position information if necessary.

Object.Name: Lagepolaritten
Position polarity parameters
Object.Comment: Dieser Parameter wird verwendet um die Polarirten der gemeldeten Positionsdaten fr spezielle Anwendungen umzuschalten. Die Polarirten werden auerhalb (z.B. am Ein- und Ausgeng) der geschlossenen Regelschleife umgeschaltet. Die Motorwelle rotiert im Uhrzeigersinn (auf die Ausgangswelle gesehen) wenn positive Positionsnderungen gegeben sind und keine Umkehrung programmiert ist.

This parameter is used to switch polarities of reported position data for specific applications. Polarities are switched outside (i.e., on the input and output) of a closed loop system. The motor shaft turns clockwise (as viewed from the output shaft) when there is a positive position command difference and no inversion is programmed.

Object.Name: Skalierungsart fr Positionsdaten
Position data scaling type
Object.Comment: Aus einer Auswahl von Skalierungsarten kann mit dem Parameter Skalierungsart eine ausgewhlt werden.
A variety of scaling methods can be selected by means of the scaling type parameter.

Object.Name: Rotations-Lageauflsung
Rotational position resolution
Object.Comment: Dieser Parameter definiert die Rotations-Lageauflsung fr alle Positions-Daten im Drive.
This parameter defines the rotational position resolution for all position data in a drive.

Object.Name: Drehmoment-Sollwert
Torque command value
Object.Comment: Wrend der Drive-Betriebsart Drehmomentkontrolle, werden Drehmoment-Sollwerte von der NC zum Drive bertragen.
During the torque control operation mode of the drive, torque command values are transferred from the control unit to the drive.

Object.Name: Positiver Drehmomenten-Grenzwert
Positive torque limit value
Object.Comment: Der Positiver Drehmomenten-Grenzwert begrenzt das maximale Drehmoment in positiver Richtung. Wenn der Drehmomenten-Grenzwert berschritten wird, setzt der Drive "T . Tlimit" in C3D (IDN 00013).
The positive torque limit value limits the maximum torque in the positive direction of rotation If the torque limit value is exceeded, the drive sets the status "T . Tlimit" in C3D (IDN 00013).

Object.Name: Negativer Drehmomenten-Grenzwert
Negative torque limit value
Object.Comment: Der negasitive Drehmomenten-Grenzwert begrenzt das maximale Drehmoment in negativer Drehrichtung. Wenn der Drehmomenten-Grenzwert berschritten wird, setzt der Drive "T . Tlimit" in C3D (IDN 00013).
The negative torque limit value limits the maximum torque in the negative direction of rotation. If the torque limit value is exceeded, the drive sets the status 'T . Tlimit' in C3D (IDN 00013)..

Object.Name: Drehmoment-Istwert
Torque feedback value
Object.Comment: Der Drehmoment-Istwert wird vom Drive zu NC bertragen.
The torque feedback value is transferred from the drive to the control unit.

Object.Name: Drehmoment-Polarittsparameter
Torque polarity parameter
Object.Comment: Dieser Parameter wird verwendet um die Polarirten der gemeldeten Drehmomentdaten fr spezielle Anwendungen umzuschalten. Die Polarirten werden auerhalb (z.B. am Ein- und Ausgeng) der geschlossenen Regelschleife umgeschaltet. Die Motorwelle rotiert im Uhrzeigersinn wenn positive Drehmomentnderungen gegeben sind und keine Umkehrung programmiert ist.

This parameter is used to switch polarities of reported torque data for specific applications. Polarities are not switched internally but externally (on the input and output) of a closed loop system. The motor shaft turns clockwise when there is a positive torque command difference and no inversion.

Object.Name: Skalierungsart fr Drehmoment- und Kraft-Daten
Torque/Force data scaling type
Object.Comment: Aus einer Auswahl von Skalierungsarten kann mit dem Parameter Skalierungsart eine ausgewhlt werden.
A variety of scaling methods can be selected by means of the scaling type parameter.

Object.Name: Bipolarer Geschwindigkeitsgrenzwert
Bipolar velocity limit value
Object.Comment: In der Drive-Betriebsart Geschwindigkeitskontrolle, bertrgt die NC die Geschwindigkeitssollwerte im Zeitabstand der NC-Zykluszeit zum Drive Der bipolare Geschwindigkeitsgrenzwert beschreibt die in beide Richtungen maximal zulssige Geschwindigkeit. Wenn der Geschwindigkeitsgrenzwert berschritten wird, meldet der Drive dies im Status durch setzen des 'ncommand > nlimit' in C3D (see IDN 00013).

In the velocity control operating mode in the drive, the control unit transfers the velocity command values to the drive in the time pattern of the control unit cycle time. The bipolar velocity limit value describes the maximum allowable velocity in both directions. If the velocity limit value is exceeded, the drive responds by setting the status 'ncommand > nlimit' in C3D (see IDN 00013).

Object.Name: Bipolarer Drehmomentgrenzwert
Bipolar torque limit value
Object.Comment: Der bipolare Drehmomentgrenzwert begrenzt das maximale Drehmoment symmetrisch in beide Richtungen. Wenn der Drehmomentgrenzwert berschritten wird, setzt der Drive im Status das 'T . Tlimit' in C3D (IDN 00013).
The bipolar torque limit value limits the maximum torque symmetrically in both directions. If the torque limit value is exceeded, the drive sets the status 'T . Tlimit' in C3D (IDN 00013).

Object.Name: Diagnose-Meldung
Diagnostic message
Object.Comment: Der aktuell relevante Operrations-Status wird mittels Diagnose-Meldungen berwacht. Die Diagnosemeldungen werden vom Drive als Text generiert und im den Operationsdaten dieser IDN gespeichert.
The currently relevant operating status is being monitored with diagnostic messages. The diagnostic messages are generated by the drive as a text and stored in the operation data of this IDN.

Object.Name: Setze Klasse 1 Diagnose zurck (pc)
Reset class 1 diagnostic (pc)
Object.Comment: When this procedure command is received by the drive via the service channel and no error exists, werden C1D, der Schnittstellen-Status, der Hersteller c1D, der Drive-Shutdown-Error (Bit 13 des Drive-StatusWorts), und der Drive-Shutdown-Mechanismus im Drive zurckgesetzt (siehe IDN 00011, IDN 00014, und IDN 00129).

Wenn dieses Prozedur-Kommando vom Drive ber den Service-Kanal empfangen wird und kein Fehler existiert, C1D, the interface status, the manufacturer's C1D, the drive shut-down error (drive status bit 13), and the drive shut-down mechanism in the drive are all reset (see IDN 00011, IDN 00014, and IDN 00129).

Object.Name: Drehzahlregler-Proportionalverstrkung
Velocity loop proportional gain
Object.Comment: Die Betriebsmige Charakteristik der Geschwindigkeitsregelschleife-Aktionszeit wird vom Hersteller definiert. Mit mem maaximalen Wert von value of 2^16 - 1(????), wird der Integrator in der Geschwindigkeitsregelschleife abgeschaltet. Die Betriebsmige Charakteristik der Drehzahlregler-Proportionalverstrkung wird vom Hersteller definiert. Die Datenlnge von 4 Byte ist fr neue Implementierungen vorgesehen.

The operational characteristic of the velocity loop integral action time is defined by the drive manufacturer. With the maximum value of 2^16 - 1 (????), the integrator in the velocity loop regulator is switched off. The operational characteristic of the velocity loop proportional gain is defined by the drive manufacturer. The 4 byte data length is preferred for new implementations.

Object.Name: Velocity loop integral action time
Object.Comment: The operational characteristic of the velocity loop integral action time is defined by the drive manufacturer. With the maximum value of 2^16 - 1 (????), the integrator in the velocity loop regulator is switched off.

Object.Name: Modulo Value
Object.Comment: This parameter defines the rotational position resolution for all position data in a drive.If the Modulo format is selected in the position data scaling factor (IDN 00076), the Modulo value defines the range that the drive & control must implement.

Object.Name: Position loop Kv-factor
Object.Comment: The KV-factor determines the gain of the position loop regulator throughout the entire velocity range.

Object.Name: Current loop proportional gain 1
Object.Comment: The current loop proportional gain 1 influences the torque/force-producing current. The mode of operation is determined by the drive manufacturer. The 4 byte data length is preferred for new implementations.

Object.Name: Current control loop integral action time 1
Object.Comment: The current integral action time 1 influences the torque/force-producing current. The mode of operation is determined by the drive manufacturer.

Object.Name: Motor peak current
Object.Comment: If the motor peak current is less than that of the amplifier, the amplifier is automatically limited to the level of the motor peak current.

Object.Name: Amplifier peak current
Object.Comment: The amplifier peak current is limited by the hardware, which means that the current for the maximum attainable torque limit value is fixed as well.

Object.Name: Motor continuous stall current
Object.Comment: The motor continuous stall current is the current at which the motor produces the continuous standstill torque according to the motor spec sheet. For all motors except for asynchronous motors, this parameter is used as a reference for all torque data and for determining motor-related current values.

Object.Name: Amplifier rated current
Object.Comment: The amplifier rated current is limited by the hardware, which means that the current for the maximum attainable torque limit value is fixed as well.

Object.Name: Maximum motor speed
Object.Comment: The maximum motor speed is listed in the motor spec sheet provided by the manufacturer.

Object.Name: Probe value 1 positive edge
Object.Comment: If an external feedback is present, the drive stores position feedback value 2 in the measuring cycle in this parameter following the positive edge of the input signal of probe 1 (see IDN 00401). If no external feedback is present, position feedback value 1 is stored. This allows the control unit to read 'probe value 1 positive edge' at a later time.

Object.Name: Probe value 1 negative edge
Object.Comment: If an external feedback is present, the drive stores osition feedback value 2 in the measuring cycle in this parameter following the positive edge of the input signal of probe 1 (see IDN 00401). If no external feedback is present, position feedback value 1 is stored. This allows the control unit to read 'probe value 1 negative edge' at a later time.

Object.Name: Positive acceleration limit value
Object.Comment: The positive acceleration parameter limits the maximum acceleration ability of the drive to the programmed value. If the velocity increases it is said to be a positive acceleration.

Object.Name: Negative acceleration limit value
Object.Comment: The negative acceleration parameter limits the maximum acceleration ability of the drive to the programmed value. If the velocity decreases it is said to be a negative acceleration.

Object.Name: Sercos interface version
Object.Comment: The operation data contains the version of the SERCOS interface specification. A version number is linked to every update. If only one of the changed or new functions of the drive is supported, then the corresponding version number must be shown. Only changes or modifications of the basic functions of SERCOS interface influence the version number.

Object.Name: Monitoring window
Object.Comment: By means of the monitoring window, the maximum position deviation, as referenced to the active position feedback value, can be defined for the position feedback value. When the position error value exceeds the maximum value of the monitoring window, the drive sets an error for excessive position deviation in C1D (S-0-0011).

Object.Name: Acceleration data scaling factor
Object.Comment: This parameter defines the scaling factor for all acceleration data in a drive.

Object.Name: Acceleration data scaling exponent
Object.Comment: This parameter defines the scaling exponent for all acceleration data in a drive.

Object.Name: Probing cycle procedure command (pc)
Object.Comment: When the master sets and enables the probing cycle procedure command, the drive reacts on the following parameters: probe 1/2 enable (IDN 00405/00406); and probe 1/2 (IDN 00401/00402) as programmed in the probe control parameter (IDN 00169). While the procedure command is activated, the control unit can start multiple measurements. If the control unit does not want any more measurements, the control unit cancels the procedure command.

Object.Name: Probe status
Object.Comment: If the drive stores one or more measurement values while the procedure command "probing cycle (IDN 00170) is activated, it simultaneously sets the assigned bit in the probe status. If probe 1 enable (IDN 00405) is reset by the control unit, the drive resets bit 0 and bit 1 of probe status. If probe 2 enable (IDN 00406) is reset by the control unit, the drive resets bit 2 and bit 3 of probe status. The drive resets all bits of the probe status when the control unit cancels the "probing cycle procedure command" (IDN 00170)

Object.Name: Lnge des konfigurierbaren Dateneintrags im AT
Length of the configurable data record in the AT
Object.Comment: Der Drive zeigt die maximale Lnge in Bytes an, die im konfigurierbaren Dateneintrag des ATs (Drive-Telegramms) im den Operationsdaten dieser IDN verarbeitet werden kann.
The drive indicates the maximum length in bytes which can be processed in the configurable data record of the AT (Drive Telegramm)in the operation data of this IDN.

Object.Name: Length of the configurable data record in the MDT
Object.Comment: The drive indicates the maximum length in bytes which can be processed in the configurable data record of the MDT in the operation data of this IDN. The drive needs to support this IDN only if it allows the application telegram in its telegram type parameter (see IDN 00015).

Object.Name: IDN-list of configurable data in the AT
Object.Comment: This list consists of the IDNs of operation data which can be processed by the drive cyclically as feedback values. The drive needs to support this list only if it allows the application telegram in its telegram type parameter (see IDN 00015).

Object.Name: IDN-list of configurable data in the MDT
Object.Comment: This list consists of the IDNs of operation data which can be processed by the drive cyclically as command values. The drive needs to support this list only if it allows the application telegram in its telegram type parameter (see IDN 00015).

Object.Name: Following distance
Object.Comment: The actual difference between the commanded velocity and actual velocity is placed in this parameter.

Object.Name: Amplifier warning temperature
Object.Comment: When the amplifier temperature exceeds the amplifier warning temperature value, the drive sets the warning bit for amplifier overtemperature in C2D (IDN 00012).

Object.Name: Motor warning temperature
Object.Comment: When the motor temperature exceeds the motor warning temperature value, the drive sets the warning bit for motor overtemperature in C2D (S-0-0012).

Object.Name: Amplifier shut down temperature
Object.Comment: When the amplifier temperature exceeds the amplifier shut-down temperature value, the drive sets the bit for amplifier overtemperature shut-down in C1D (IDN 00011).

Object.Name: Motor shut down temperature
Object.Comment: When the motor temperature exceeds the motor shut-down temperature value, the drive sets the bit for motor overtemperature shut-down in C1D (IDN 00011).

Object.Name: Drive on delay time
Object.Comment: After torque is activated (bit 14, drive status is set) "drive on delay time" is started. The drive follows the command values after the "drive on delay time" has elapsed.

Object.Name: Drive off delay time
Object.Comment: After "drive off" (bit 15 of the master control word) is reset and nmin is reached, the drive off delay time is started and the locking of the brake is initiated. The torque remains activated in the drive until this drive off delay time is elapsed. Example: Used as break delay time (clamping or release).

Object.Name: Multiplication factor 1
Object.Comment: Multiplication Factor 1 defines the factor that the motor feedback signal is multiplied by in the drive (see IDN 00116). Multiplication factor 1 can also be determined by the drive, taking the Maximum travel range (IDN 00278) into account. The drive-internal resolution for the motor encoder is determined from the resolution of feedback 1 (IDN 00116) and multiplication factor 1.

Object.Name: Multiplication factor 2
Object.Comment: Multiplication Factor 2 defines the factor that the EXTERNAL feedback signal is multiplied by in the drive (see IDN 00117). Multiplication factor 2 can also be determined by the drive, taking the Maximum travel range (IDN 00278) into account. The drive-internal resolution for the external encoder is determined from the resolution of feedback 2 (IDN 00117) and multiplication factor 2.

Object.Name: Password
Object.Comment: SERCOS interface supports passwords that can be used to write protect selected parameters stored in the drive. IDN 00267 is used to modify passwords, as well as enable and disable write protection

Object.Name: Maximum drive off delay time
Object.Comment: After "drive off" (bit 15, control word) is reset, the maximum drive off delay time is started. After the maximum drive off delay time is elapsed, the locking of the brake is initiated and the torque is disabled.

Object.Name: Drive enable delay time
Object.Comment: When "drive enable" is set (bits 14, control word) the "drive enable delay time" is started. Motor current (torque) will first be activated after this time delay. The enable delay is required at use of a contactor in the motor cable.

Object.Name: Velocity feed forward gain
Object.Comment: Velocity feed forward is effective in the operation mode "Position control without following error (lagless)", and serves to reduce the velocity-dependent following error.

Object.Name: Velocity error
Object.Comment: The actual difference between the commanded velocity and actual velocity is placed in this parameter.

Object.Name: Drive Halt acceleration bipolar
Object.Comment: Bipolar jerk limits the maximum rate of change of acceleration. Programming a value of zero will cause jerk limiting to be deactivated.

Object.Name: Diagnostic numbers list
Object.Comment: The drive records every change of the diagnostic number into this list. The list is organized as a ring buffer. When the list is read via the service channel, the drive will position the last diagnostic recorded as the first element of the list.

Object.Name: DC bus voltage
Object.Comment: The drives DC (intermediate) bus voltage value is placed in this parameter.

Object.Name: DC bus current
Object.Comment: The drive places the measured (actual) DC (intermediate) bus current in this parameter.

Object.Name: Motor temperature
Object.Comment: The drive places the measured (actual) motor temperature in this parameter.

Object.Name: Amplifier temperature
Object.Comment: The drive places the measured (actual) amplifier temperature (output stage) in this parameter.

Object.Name: Diagnostic number
Object.Comment: For every diagnostic, the drive stores a manufacturer specific code in the diagnostic number parameter. Using this, the operator interface has the ability to display diagnostic message text in languages not supported by the drive

Object.Name: Probe 1 enable
Object.Comment: This parameter is used to assign an IDN to probe 1 enable. This allows the status "probe 1 enable" to be assigned to a real-time control bit (see IDN 00301). Probe 1 enable is checked by the drive only as long as the procedure command "probing cycle" (IDN 00170) is active. For a new probing cycle with the same edge of probe 1 the control unit has to reset probe 1 enable to "0" and set it to "1" (see 11.4). Bit 0 is defined for operation data only. (For more details see IDN 00179.)

Object.Name: Probe 1 positive latched
Object.Comment: This parameter is used to assign an IDN to probe 1 positive latched. This allows the status "probe 1 positive latched" to be assigned to a real-time status bit (see S-0-0305). Bit 0 of this parameter is set by the drive only if the procedure command "probing cycle" (S-0-0170) is active, the signal "probe 1 enable" (S-0-0405) is set to 1 and the positive edge of "probe 1" (S-0-0401) is registered. Simultaneously the drive stores the position feedback value in "probe 1 positive edge" (S-0-0130) (see clause 13.7). The drive resets this bit when the control unit cancels the procedure command "probing cycle" or when probe 1 enable is reset to 0. Bit 0 is defined for operation data only. (For more details see S-0-0179.)

Object.Name: Probe 1 negative latched
Object.Comment: This parameter is used to assign an IDN to probe 1 negative latched. This allows the status "probe 1 negative latched" to be assigned a real-time status bit (see S-0-0305). Bit 0 of this parameter is set by the drive only if the procedure command "probing cycle" (S-0-0170) is active, the signal "probe 1 enable" (S- 0-0405) is set to 1 and the negative edge of "probe 1" (S-0-0401) is registered. Simultaneously the drive stores the position feedback value in "probe 1 negative edge" (S-0-0131) (see clause 13.7). The drive resets this bit when the control unit cancels the procedure command "probing cycle" or when probe 1 enable is reset to 0. Bit 0 is defined for operation data only. (For more details see S-0-0179.)

Object.Name: Switching frequency of the IGBT module
Object.Comment: This parameter defines the switching frequency of the IGBT module.

Object.Name: Current ctrl cycle time
Object.Comment: This parameter defines the current ctrl cycle time.

Object.Name: Velocity ctrl cycle time
Object.Comment: This parameter defines the velocity control cycle time.

Object.Name: Position ctrl cycle time
Object.Comment: This parameter defines the position control cycle time.

Object.Name: Number of pole pairs/pole pair distance
Max motor speed with max torque
Channel peak current
Object.Comment: The amplifier peak current is limited by the hardware, which means that the current for the maximum attainable torque limit value is fixed as well.

Object.Name: Channel rated current
Object.Comment: The amplifier rated current is limited by the hardware, which means that the current for the maximum attainable torque limit value is fixed as well.

Object.Name: Configured channel peak current
Object.Comment: The value of S-0-0110 is distributed to the 2 channels of the device.

Object.Name: Configured channel current
Object.Comment: The value of S-0-0110 is distributed to the 2 channels of the device.

Object.Name: Digital motor name plate
Object.Comment: The motor data set stored in the feedback device of the motor.

Object.Name: Calibrate commutation offset (pc)
Object.Comment: Calibrate the commutation offset

Object.Name: Feedback 1: Save position offset (pc)
Object.Comment: Feedback device: Save position offset (pc)

Object.Name: Feedback 1: Save digital name plate (pc)
Object.Comment: Feedback device: Save motor parameter (pc)

Object.Name: Motor and feedback connection check parameter
Feedback 1: Absolute sin/cos position calculation parameter
Object.Comment: engl.

P-0-0171 dient der Ermittlung des analogen absoluten Teiles des Positionswertes. Die folgenden Schritte zeigen die Berechnung: 1. 20bit (1 Umdr.) des 32bit Positionswertes ausmaskieren -> S-0-0051 & 0xFFFFF 2. Multiplikation des Positionswertes mit dem Bruch -> * (Numerator/Denominator) 3. Analogen absoluten Teil mittels der Maske ausmaskieren -> & Mask 4. Multiplikation des analogen absoluten Teiles mit dem Kehrwert des Bruches -> * Denominator/Numerator

Object.Name: Warning level: Actual power internal brake resitor
Warning level: Actual power external brake resitor
External DC link current
Object.Comment: The drive places the actual external DC link current in this parameter.

Object.Name: Probe 1 time negaitve edge
Object.Comment: The drive stores the system time of the negative edge of probe 1 in this parameter.

Object.Name: Probe 1 time difference: reference switch to index
Object.Comment: The time difference between the reference switch signal and the index signal.

Object.Name: PLL ctrl error
Object.Comment: The current PLL ctrl error

Object.Name: Software versions
Object.Comment: A collection of the device component software versions

Object.Name: Device component hardware Id's
Object.Comment: A collection of the device component hardware Id's

Object.Name: Error reaction delay time
Object.Comment: During the error reaction delay time the NC has the possibility to stop the axis. If the time is elapsed, the drive stops the axis.

Object.Name: Factory Settings
Object.Comment: A collection of the device factory settings.

Object.Name: Current calibration parameter
Object.Comment: The operation data of the manufacturer version contains the actual firmware version and additional information of the device. The structure of the manufacturer version is not specified.
